The Board ensures that issues or matters requlring shareholders’ approval are tabled in the form of separate and distinct resolutions at general meetings on each distlhct issue. Explanatory notes are included in the AGM notice to provide further information on the agenda items of the AGM. Resolutlons tabled at general meetings are voted by poll and the number of votes cast for and against each resolution and the respective percentage will be disclosed. The Company will appoint an independent external party as scrutineer for the poll voting process. Prior to the commencement of the general meeting, the scrutlneer would review the proxies and proxy process. Shareholders were informed of the voting process at each general meeting. Detailed results of the poll votes for each resolution will be promptly disclosed on the SGXNET after the general meetings. The company secretary will prepare minutes of general meetings held which will be made available to shareholders upon request
